I have a theory, and it may have been mentioned already.  I just don't feel like going comment combing to find it.  My theory is Peanut Butter has a lot of oil in it.  Products using it will use reduced oil versions instead of the full oil versions.  Jarred PB has high content of oil hence why it wont freeze dry, Ice Creams, Candy Bars and other treats use more powder content/less oil.  PB powder is basically dried peanut butter it just has none of the oil or water contents you would normally see since they have been pressed out. I used to make nonfat PB with PB2-Dried PB product types. I believe the more powdery PB being used is reconstituting into the ice creams you are using in some cases...Something to consider..
